The body of a baby girl was found on Friday afternoon, wrapped in a plastic bag at an intersection in Raslouw, Centurion, paramedics said. ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring said that when paramedics arrived on the scene at around 3.30pm they found the body of a newborn baby girl lying wrapped in a plastic bag. It was evident that the baby had been dead for some time. Unfortunately, nothing could be done for the child and she was declared dead on the scene. It is believed that that the little girl s body was spotted by a member of public who had been passing by. Meiring said that the details surrounding the incident was unknown and would be investigated by local authorities who were on the scene.